genresAdvancedInfo.name: musica eletronica brasileira
genresAdvancedInfo.description: This is a subgenre of electronic music that originated in Brazil in the 1990s. It combines elements of traditional Brazilian music with electronic beats and sounds. It often features the use of the berimbau, a traditional Brazilian instrument, and incorporates elements of samba and bossa nova.
